s' '**/package.json'`)\",\n        \"`dotnet build src/Skoruba.Duende.IdentityServer.Admin.sln --configuration Release` succeeds with no new warnings beyond upstream rc1 baseline\",\n        \"All `tests/*` test projects pass (`dotnet test` on UnitTests, IntegrationTests, STS.IntegrationTests)\",\n        \"Typecheck passes (dotnet build with no errors)\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"passes\": true,\n      \"notes\": \"Verified 2026-05-11: Directory.Build.props <Version> set to 3.0.0-FMFX.1. Build succeeded (0 errors, 0 warnings). All 314 tests pass (174 unit + 39 API unit + 78 API integration + 23 STS integration).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-003\",\n      \"title\": \"Update publish workflow to target FreemarketFX GitHub Packages\",\n      \"description\": \"As a release engineer, I want the NuGet publish workflow on the new branch to push to the FreemarketFX GitHub Packages feed (not upstream's destination), so subsequent stories can produce consumable 3.0.0-FMFX.N packages.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"Publish workflow YAML in `.github/workflows/` runs `dotnet pack` and `dotnet nuget push` targeting `https://nuget.pkg.github.com/FreemarketFX/index.json`\",\n        \"Authentication uses the FreemarketFX GitHub Packages publish secret name mirroring the previous fork's publish workflow on old `main`\",\n        \"Workflow triggers include push/release for `feature/rebase-onto-3.0.0-rc1` (and `main` once promoted)\",\n        \"Workflow does NOT push from upstream-tracking branches (no `release/3.0.0-rc1` or `release/*` triggers on the publish job)\",\n        \"Workflow YAML is syntactically valid (verified via `actionlint` or equivalent, or visual inspection if no linter available)\",\n        \"`dotnet build src/Skoruba.Duende.IdentityServer.Admin.sln --configuration Release` succeeds\",\n        \"All `tests/*` test projects pass\",\n        \"Typecheck passes (dotnet build with no errors)\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 3,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-004\",\n      \"title\": \"Re-enable CodeQL workflow on the new branch\",\n      \"description\": \"As a security owner, I want CodeQL scanning enabled on the new branch from day one so security findings track from the baseline, not from when bespoke code lands.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"A CodeQL workflow file exists in `.github/workflows/` (ported from the previous fork's `chore(FMFX-8682): Setup GitHub Advanced Security` commit if not already present from upstream)\",\n        \"Workflow triggers on push and pull_request targeting `feature/rebase-onto-3.0.0-rc1`\",\n        \"Languages list includes both `csharp` and `javascript-typescript` (covers the React SPA)\",\n        \"CodeQL config file (if used) has no broken globs; YAML is syntactically valid (visual inspection or actionlint)\",\n        \"`dotnet build src/Skoruba.Duende.IdentityServer.Admin.sln --configuration Release` succeeds\",\n        \"All `tests/*` test projects pass\",\n        \"Typecheck passes (dotnet build with no errors)\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 4,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-005\",\n      \"title\": \"Update README with new baseline and re-base strategy\",\n      \"description\": \"As anyone landing on the repo, I want the README to make clear that this is now a fork of upstream release/3.0.0-rc1, that the long-lived branch has changed, and what the re-base plan is, so I don't act on stale assumptions from the old 1.2.0-based code.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"`README.md` has a 'Freemarket fork' section at the top stating: upstream baseline is `skoruba/Duende.IdentityServer.Admin@release/3.0.0-rc1`\",\n        \"README states the active branch is `feature/rebase-onto-3.0.0-rc1` (will become `main` after the rebase epic completes)\",\n        \"README states the package versioning convention `3.0.0-FMFX.N`\",\n        \"README states the re-base plan: re-base onto stable `3.0.0` once Skoruba tags it\",\n        \"README links to `CLAUDE.md` in this repo and to `Freemarket.Identity/CLEANUP-PLAN.md` for the epic-level plan\",\n        \"No upstream README content deleted beyond what's needed to avoid direct contradiction with the Freemarket fork section\",\n        \"`dotnet build src/Skoruba.Duende.IdentityServer.Admin.sln --configuration Release` succeeds\",\n        \"All `tests/*` test projects pass\",\n        \"Typecheck passes (dotnet build with no errors)\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 5,\n      \"passes\": false,\n      \"notes\": \"\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"US-006\",\n      \"title\": \"Prepare branch for PR (do not push, do not merge)\",\n      \"description\": \"As the developer running this story, I want the branch in a clean, reviewable state with all commits clearly attributable, so the human reviewer can verify each step before pushing or opening a PR.\",\n      \"acceptanceCriteria\": [\n        \"`git status` shows a clean working tree on `feature/rebase-onto-3.0.0-rc1`\",\n        \"`git log feature/rebase-onto-3.0.0-rc1 ^upstream/release/3.0.0-rc1 --oneline` shows only commits from US-001 through US-005 plus the setup commits (claude-shared subtree add + CLAUDE.md + PRD)\",\n        \"Each commit message in that range follows Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, etc.) and ends with the standard `Co-Authored-By: Claude (<model-id>) <noreply@anthropic.com>` trailer\",\n        \"No `git push` to origin has been executed; no PR has been opened\",\n        \"`dotnet build src/Skoruba.Duende.IdentityServer.Admin.sln --configuration Release` succeeds\",\n        \"All `tests/*` test projects pass\",\n        \"Typecheck passes (dotnet build with no errors)\",\n        \"Tests pass\"\n      ],\n      \"priority\": 6,\n      \"p